Not as good as I had thought. It was a low budget film so ofcourse nothing spectacular came out of it. The lesbian storyline was kinda rushed, they go from meeting at a club to living together? Then it looked like the Dom and her friend were going to get together, then there's the script and pressure to quit the business. There is just too much going on in the movie that they leave parts out. The Lesbian couple is a movie on it's own...well could have been there as no need for all the other junk. Some scenes are pointless

I stumbled across this movie on netflix and thought it was awesome.  It's super stylized and interesting to look at, and the actors (all relatively unknown) do a great job.  One of the most honest portrayals of lesbianism I've seen in a movie recently.  Nicole Laliberte, who stars in it, looks amazing and is a super unique actress.

This was an interesting movie. I enjoyed the friendships that the women shared. Some of the acting wasn't that great. It wasn't all characters but some were not as strong as others. Overall, I do think it was a good movie and look forward to seeing more from this talented screenwriter.
